Taiwan Stocks: Evergreen, Formosa Plastics, Inventec Appliances

-- B y   W e i y i   L i m
-- 
2011-03-23T01:34:35Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-23/everlight-evergreen-formosa-plastics-taiwan-stocks-preview.html
Stocks of the following companies
may have unusual moves in  Taiwan  trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses and prices are as of 9:27 a.m. local time.  The Taiex Index rose 2.99, or 0.04 percent, to 8,511.03.  EVA Airways Corp. (2618)  (2618 TT) gained 2.9 percent to NT$24.60,
the highest since March 14. Taiwan’s second-biggest carrier
reported 2010 net income of NT$12 billion ($406 million),
compared with a loss of NT$2.84 billion a year earlier, the
Taoyuan-based company said in a statement to the Taiwan stock
exchange. The company plans to pay a cash dividend of NT$1 per
share on 2010 earnings, along with a stock dividend of 100
shares for every 1,000 shares held by investors.  Evergreen Marine Corp. (2603 TT) increased 1.8 percent to
NT$25.05, the highest since March 7. The listed unit of  Asia ’s
biggest container line posted net income of NT$3.49 billion in
the fourth quarter, compared with a net loss of NT$2.56 billion
a year earlier, according to Bloomberg calculations based on
full-year results announced yesterday by the Taipei-based
company. Profit beat the NT$2.47 billion median estimate of
eight analyst estimates compiled by Bloomberg.  Formosa Plastics Corp. (1301)  (1301 TT) advanced 1 percent to
NT$101.50. The board of Taiwan’s largest maker of polyvinyl
chloride approved a plan to pay a cash dividend of NT$6.80 per
share on its 2010 earnings, the company said in a statement to
the Taiwan stock exchange.  Inventec Corp. (2356 TT) rose 2.7 percent to NT$15.10, the
most since Dec. 6. The notebook computer maker agreed to buy the
remaining shares of affiliate  Inventec Appliances Corp. (3367)  (3367
TT), taking full control of the maker of mobile phones and Apple
Inc. iPods, the companies said. Inventec Appliances surged 6.8
percent, the biggest jump since Dec. 2, to NT$21.90.  Yulon Motor Co. (2201 TT) advanced 0.9 percent to NT$55.
The automaker’s board approved plan to invest an additional 600
million yuan ($91.5 million) in its China plant, the Miaoli,
Taiwan-based company said in an exchange statement.  To contact the reporter on this story:
